description: The image depicts a writer slumped over a desk, surrounded by crumpled papers. The writer is grappling with the opening line of a novel titled "Moby Dick". Each discarded paper shows a variation on the famous opening phrase "Call me Ishmael", substituting other names like Bill, Larry, Al, Roger, and Warren. This absurd repetition highlights the creative struggle and the pressure to invent an iconic first sentence. The scene ironically contrasts the singular success of Melville's opening with a multitude of less inspired alternatives.
